Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces, if necessary. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Zest 1 lime and quarter both.

== Ginger Lime Rice ==

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1 1/2 cups water.

== Candied Peanuts ==

While rice cooks, add @peanuts{1/2%ounce}, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and @water{2%tablespoon} to a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until water has evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wash out pan.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2 tsp sugar and 3 TBSP water.

== Stir-Fry ==

Heat a large drizzle of oil in same #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion; season with salt and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until slightly tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add broccoli and a splash of water. Cover and steam until broccoli is bright green, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Uncover and add remaining ginger. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute} more.

To pan with veggies, add @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{2%tablespoon}, @water{1/4%cup}, and lime juice to taste.

Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened and veggies are coated, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in half the cilantro. Turn off heat.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1/3 cup water.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and lime zest to taste. Season with salt. Divide between #bowls{}.

Top rice with stir-fry, peanuts, @crispy fried onions{1}, and remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2 TBSP butter.